<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 29 at 7:30PM EDT until July 29 at 10:00PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR
NORTHERN CHARLOTTE COUNTY WILL EXPIRE AT 730 PM EDT...
The storms which prompted the warning have weakened below severe
limits, and have exited the warned area. Therefore, the warning will
be allowed to expire.  However heavy rain is still possible with
these thunderstorms.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
central and south central Virginia.</description>
